Package: creditmodel
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2019-04-05
Title: Functions and tools designed to develop credit risk models
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Dong", family = "Fan",email = "fdp@pku.edu.cn",role = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Dongping Fan <fdp@pku.edu.cn> 
Description: CreditModel package is a set of integrated tools designed to help you be more productive and easier develop credit risk models, such as traditional scorecard based on logistic regression, machine learning models based on GBDT and XGboost.It includes some useful and efficient functions for automatic data cleaning, variable derivation, data analysis, feature selection, scorecard building, data visualization and a variety of robust tools for binning,one-hot-encoding,de-one-hot-encoding, IV\PSI\K-S\Lift\Gini caculating and ploting. It also provides some functions for vintage analysis,delinquency.
Depends: R(>= 3.3.0)
